application

Class EBookingController

  • java.lang.Object
    • application.EBookingController

  • public class EBookingController
extends java.lang.Object
    This class gives the employee access to the cinema room representation for a given projection time. The seatings are represented with checkBoxes that are different if the seat is booked or available.
    Author:
    Federico Ziviani

        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - cannot connect to database when the connection to the database fails.

      • back

        public void back(javafx.event.ActionEvent e)
        Loads back this previous page. Before reloading it it calls this controller to set the text of the movie title. set the description to the movie description. And set the image view to the movie image. The method to fill the combo is called from the controller home. That in this case is the Employee Home page.
        Parameters:
        e - event that occurs when the home button is clicked.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - of an invalid fxml file when it tries to loads the page in a wrong format.

      • home

        public void home(javafx.event.ActionEvent e)
        Loads the home page. The movies' titles will still be in the comboBox. The method to fill the combo is called from the controller home. That in this case is the Employee Home page.
        Parameters:
        e - the action to be executed when the home button is clicked.
        Throws:
        the - Exception of an invalid fxml file when it tries to loads the page in a wrong format.
